t: O*p sing unto the Lord*s a new song; for he hath done marvellous things: his right hand, and his holy arm, hath gotten him the victory.
The*p Lord*s hath made known his salvation: his righteousness hath he openly shewed in the sight of the heathen.
He*p hath remembered his mercy and his truth toward the house of Israel: all the ends of the earth have seen the salvation of our God.
Make*p a joyful noise unto the Lord,*s all the earth: make a loud noise, and rejoice, and sing praise.
Sing*p unto the Lord*s with the harp; with the harp, and the voice of a psalm.
With*p trumpets and sound of cornet make a joyful noise before the Lord,*s the King.
Let*p the sea roar, and the fulness thereof; the world, and they that dwell therein.
Let*p the floods clap their hands: let the hills be joyful together
Before*p the Lord;*s for he cometh to judge the earth: with righteousness shall he judge the world, and the people with equity.
